quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  17,97,"And he whom Allâh guides, he is led aright; but he whom He sends astray, for such you will find no Auliyâ’ (helpers and protectors), besides Him, and We shall gather them together on the Day of Resurrection on their faces,{1}blind, dumb and deaf; their abode will be Hell; whenever it abates, We shall increase for them the fierceness of the Fire.",footnotes:1:{17:97} Narrated Anas bin Mâlik رضي الله عنه: A man said, "O Allâh’s Prophet! Will Allâh gather a disbeliever (prone) on his face on the Day of Resurrection?" He صلى الله عليه وسلم said, "Will not the One Who made him walk on his feet in this world, be able to make him walk on his face on the Day of Resurrection?" (Qatâdah, a subnarrator, said: "Yes, by the Power of Our Lord!") (Sahih Al Bukhri, Vol. 6, Hadith No.283).
  17,98,"That is their recompense, because they denied Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) and said: "
  17,99,"See they not that Allâh, Who created the heavens and the earth, is Able to create the like of them. And He has decreed for them an appointed term, whereof there is no doubt. But the Zâlimûn (polytheists and wrong-doers) refuse (the truth - the Message of Islâmic Monotheism, and accept nothing) but disbelief."
  18,64,"[Mûsâ (Moses)] said: "
  18,65,"Then they found one of Our slaves, on whom We had bestowed mercy from Us, and whom We had taught knowledge from Us."
  18,66,"Mûsâ (Moses) said to him (Khidr): "
  19,25,""
  19,26,""
  19,27,"Then she brought him (the baby) to her people, carrying him. They said: "
  20,7,"And if you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) speak (the invocation) aloud, then verily, He knows the secret and that which is yet more hidden."
  20,8,"Allâh! Lâ ilâha illa Huwa (none has the right to be worshipped but He)! To Him belong the Best Names.{1}",footnotes:1:{20:8} See the footnote of (Verse 7:180).
  20,9,"And has there come to you the story of Mûsâ (Moses)?"